
[1]bardesanists

   BARDES'ANISTS, n. A sect of heretics, who sprung from Bardesanes, of
   Edessa, in Mesopotamia, in the 2d century, who taught that the actions
   of men depend on fate, to which God himself is subject. His followers
   went farther, and denied the incarnation of Christ and the
   resurrection.
